	year = {2007},
	abstract = {Support vector machines (SVM) is a new machine learning method, and it has the ability to approximate nonlinear functions with arbitrary accuracy. Right setting parameters are very crucial to learning results and generalization ability of SVM. In this paper, parameters selection is regarded as a compound optimization problem and a modified differential evolution (MDE) algorithm is applied to search the optimal parameters. The modified differential evolution adopts a time-varying crossover probability strategy, which can improve the global convergence ability and robustness of the algorithm. Various examples are simulated and the experiment results demonstrate that this proposed approach has better approximation performance than other approaches.},
